WHEREHOO INSTALLATION NOTESInstall LinuxInstall Java 1.3Install ANT (jakarta.apache.org/ant)	download the source, jakarta-ant-1.4.1.src.tar.gz	cd /tmp	tar -zxvf jakarta-ant-1.4.1.src.tar.gz	export ANT_HOME=/usr/local/ant   (or setenv /usr/local/ant)	export JAVA_HOME=/usr/local/jdk-1.3 (powerbook: setenv JAVA_HOME /usr)	export PATH=${PATH}:${ANT_HOME}/bin	./build.sh	./build.sh installInstall Postgresql (postgresql.org, ftp://ftp3.us.postgresql.org)	cd /tmp	tar -zxvf postgresql-7.1.3.tar.gz	cd postgresql-7.1.3	(see INSTALL for much of the below)	(be sure path includes ANT's /bin directory - was exported above)	./configure --with-java	gmake	su	/usr/sbin/adduser postgres	gmake install (installs to /usr/local/pgsql)	cd /usr/local/pgsql	chown postgres * -R	su - postgres	(see INSTALL for the 4 init and startup commands)		/usr/local/pgsql/bin/initdb -D /usr/local/pgsql/data	/usr/local/pgsql/bin/postmaster -D /usr/local/pgsql/data >logfile 2>&1 &	/usr/local/pgsql/bin/createdb test	/usr/local/pgsql/bin/psql test	OR TO ADD TCP/IP ACCESS CHANGE LINE 2 ABOVE:	usr/local/pgsql/bin/postmaster -i -D /usr/local/pgsql/data >logfile 2>&1 &	OR FOR TCP ACCESS AND WORKABLE LOGGING (TO A DIR THAT USER 'postgres' CAN WRITE)	/usr/local/pgsql/bin/postmaster -i -D /usr/local/pgsql/data >/usr/local/pgsql/data/logfile 2>&1 &My home machine is:	jyoull.dyndns.org and some work stuff is there in 'jim' home directoryDatabases are in:	/usr/local/pgsql/data/base/	Dump in the data from the file datadir.tar 	cd /usr/local/pgsql/data	tar -xvf datadir.tar	su	chown postgres * -RTo access:	su postgres	bin/psql -d testStartup script	/etc/rc.d/init.d/postgresql (get from jyoull.dyndns.org)	add it in via chkconfigInstall Wherehoo Server (WHServer)	/home/whserver (?)	classpath to postgresql driveWHEREHOO SERVER *MUST* USE THE 7.1-1.1 driver located in:	/usr/local/pgsql/share/java/jdbc7.1-1.1.jar	Startup script for Wherehoo Server is:#!/bin/shexport CLASSPATH=.:/usr/local/pgsql/share/java/jdbc7.1-1.1.jarjava WHServer &